<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-093-128 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 175 121</DOCID><JOURNAL>Journal of Systems Management  August 1991 v42 n8 p21(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Techniques in illustrating systems profits. (making businesspresentations) (Looking Back) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Stevens, Robert I.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Information systems (IS) professionals help firms minimize costsand maximize profits by making sure systems are developed to runefficiently and effectively.andP;  It is the job of IS managers tocommunicate about these efforts to firm directors.andP;  An effectivetechnique for making the necessary business presentation includeswriting down a firm's last full year's sales figure, notingcompany profit, dividing the profit into the sales figure, anddetermining how savings from IS contributed to the profit amount.andO;Not every project generates clear savings, but it is also possibleto consider person-hours saved.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     GuidelinesInformation systemsSystem developmentSystems AnalysisProject managementBudgetingPresentationsCost Reduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>